tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glycosuria, ketonuria, and low urine specific gravity, suggesting impaired renal function with possible nephropathy. Low HbA1c with normoglycemia may indicate recent hypoglycemia or anemia. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) raise suspicion for urinary tract pathology, though no infection markers are present. Recommend further renal evaluation and clinical correlation for possible chronic kidney disease and metabolic disturbances.
